Hello,

Today, we're releasing our first agentic coding model and a new interface f=
or working with many agents in parallel.

********************************
Composer, our first coding model
********************************

Composer ( https://cursor.com/blog/composer ) is a frontier model that is 4=
x faster than similarly intelligent models.

The model is built for low-latency agentic coding in Cursor, and completes =
most turns in under 30 seconds.

Try it in Cursor ( cursor://anysphere.cursor-deeplink/prompt?text=3DResearc=
h+and+find+one+bug+in+this+codebase )

***************************
A new multi-agent interface
***************************

We=E2=80=99ve added an entirely new interface in Cursor, designed around ag=
ents rather than files. So you can focus on the outcomes you want while age=
nts take care of the details. When you need to dive deep into the code, you=
 can easily switch back to the classic IDE.

Cursor 2.0 makes it easy to run many agents in parallel without them interf=
ering with one another, powered by Git worktrees or remote machines. We=E2=80=
=99ve even found that having multiple models attempt the same problem and p=
icking the best result significantly improves the final output, especially =
for harder tasks.

****************
Embedded browser
****************

Browser is now embedded in-editor, including powerful new tools to select e=
lements, full dev tools, and MCP controls for the agent.

********************
Improved code review
********************

You can now also see all of the changes an agent has made across your codeb=
ase in a single place instead of jumping across different files.

********
And more
********

* Voice mode for native speech to text
* Improved language server performance and text rendering throughout the ap=
p
* Deeplinks for rules & commands
* Plan mode for Background Agents
* New security controls for Enterprise

Cursor 2.0 is now available for download ( http://cursor.com/download ), an=
d you can read about all changes in our changelog ( https://cursor.com/chan=
gelog/2-0 ).

=C2=A0

We=E2=80=99re excited to hear what you think!

- Cursor Team

